content.description: Splitter fist crack.  Roof right at the start, 2nd roof mid wall.
content.protection: Free: bring tricams, large gear   Aid: hooks pecker and a sling for horns
content.location: Take the orange trail from the Woodberry Senior Center parking lot. When the trail hooks left you will see a climber Trail going straight. Continue 2 to 3 minutes until you see a prominent system of roofs on the left. This climb is just short of the giant 40 foot wide roof. You know you are there if you are looking at a little roof about chest height for the start of the route

content.description: Crag of 120 routes, of which roughly 100 are on private property which has been closed to climbing by the owner.
